---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import TldrBox from '../../components/TldrBox.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import ToolReview from '../../components/ToolReview.astro';
import { site, description, pageTitle } from '../../content';
import { useCaseBySlug } from '../../data/use-cases';
import { appBySlug } from '../../data/apps';

const uc = useCaseBySlug('segmentation')!;
const path = '/use-cases/segmentation';
const title = pageTitle(site, 'use-cases/segmentation');
const desc = description(site, 'use-cases/segmentation');

const featuredSlugs = ['sequenzy', 'klaviyo', 'drip', 'activecampaign', 'omnisend'];
const featuredApps = featuredSlugs.map((s) => appBySlug(s)!).filter(Boolean);

const comparisonApps = [
  'sequenzy', 'klaviyo', 'drip', 'activecampaign', 'omnisend', 'sendlane',
  'yotpo-email-sms', 'mailchimp', 'brevo', 'marsello',
].map((s) => appBySlug(s)!).filter(Boolean);

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What Shopify email tool has the best segmentation for lifecycle email?',
    answer: 'Klaviyo ranks first for behavioral segmentation depth — Shopify event sync, predictive scores, and complex boolean segments at scale. Sequenzy wins for strategy-first segment playbooks that map segments to actions without blank canvas paralysis. Drip suits visual segment-to-flow mapping for operators who audit logic on canvas.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What segments should every Shopify store define first?',
    answer: 'Buyers versus non-buyers; full-price loyalists versus discount-sensitive; VIP by RFM; engaged versus unengaged email; gift versus self-purchase; active subscription versus one-time. Specialty tea merchants add harvest preference; climbing gear adds skill level from quiz or purchase history.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How often should segments be audited?',
    answer: 'Weekly spot-check on active campaign segments; monthly prune stale definitions; quarterly RFM recalculation for VIP and winback. Segments without defined actions should be deleted — clutter causes overlap and wrong sends.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What is segment overlap and why does it matter?',
    answer: 'Customer in VIP and winback and cart simultaneously without priority rules gets triple discount risk. Define flow priority: cart over winback over newsletter promo. Document overlap percentage monthly — target under 5% unhandled overlap on high-value segments.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Should segmentation use tags or behavior?',
    answer: 'Behavior primary — orders, views, email engagement. Tags supplement for preferences quiz results, gift buyer, switch preference. Tag-only segments without behavior go stale when tags are not maintained.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How does segmentation power newsletters versus lifecycle?',
    answer: 'Newsletter: interest-based — genre for vinyl, roast preference for coffee. Lifecycle: stage-based — welcome, post-purchase, replenishment. Same platform, different segment definitions. Dynamic content blocks let one newsletter template serve multiple interest segments.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can small Shopify stores skip advanced segmentation?',
    answer: 'Start with five core segments — buyers, non-buyers, engaged, VIP, discount-sensitive. Enough for welcome branching and cart caps until 500 orders per month. Complexity should grow with catalog and channel mix, not ahead of it.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do segments connect to transactional email?',
    answer: 'Transactional sends generally ignore marketing segments — order confirmation goes to all buyers. Marketing segments control lifecycle and newsletter; transactional uses order events. Exception: locale and market segments for Shopify Markets shipping content in transactional templates.',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/use-cases" class="text-sm font-bold text-[#9a5b16] hover:text-[#24170f]">← All use cases</a>
      <p class="catalog-kicker mt-6">Segmentation</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">Best Shopify email tools for segmentation</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-9 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Segmentation is the operating system for newsletters, lifecycle flows, and targeted campaigns — not a folder of unused lists. A specialty tea merchant needs harvest preference and brewing frequency segments; a climbing gear shop needs skill level and seasonality; a vinyl label needs genre collector versus casual listener. The right Shopify email tool builds behavior-first segments, resolves overlap with priority rules, and connects every segment to an defined action.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-[#5d3a1d]">
        This playbook ranks email tools for {uc.job}. We evaluated Shopify event sync, segment freshness, overlap handling, and newsletter versus lifecycle split — not which platform lets you create the most segments without sending to them. Good segmentation reduces send volume while increasing revenue per send — bad segmentation multiplies lists nobody uses while collision rules silently double-discount VIP cart abandoners.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/apps">Full tool catalog</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/use-cases/vip-segments">VIP segments</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/compare/klaviyo-vs-drip">Klaviyo vs Drip</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox
      title="Top Shopify email tools for segmentation"
      picks={[
        { label: 'Best overall', tool: 'Klaviyo', reason: 'Deepest Shopify behavioral segmentation, predictive scores, and real-time segment updates at scale.' },
        { label: 'Best strategy speed', tool: 'Sequenzy', reason: 'Segment playbooks mapped to lifecycle actions with agent-first definitions and overlap suppression.' },
        { label: 'Best workflow control', tool: 'Drip', reason: 'Visual segment-to-flow mapping with explicit tags and audit-friendly canvas.' },
        { label: 'Best CRM depth', tool: 'ActiveCampaign', reason: 'Contact scoring and CRM-style segmentation when sales touchpoints precede purchase.' },
        { label: 'Best fast setup', tool: 'Omnisend', reason: 'Prebuilt segments for buyers, cart abandoners, and engaged lists live in hours.' },
      ]}
    />

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Three segmentation merchant scenarios</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario A — Specialty tea merchant, harvest and habit segments.</strong> Klaviyo segments: oolong buyers, daily brewers from post-purchase survey, gift tin purchasers excluded from replenishment. Newsletter dynamic blocks show harvest origin matching purchase history. Campaign revenue per recipient up 34% versus undifferentiated list blasts.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario B — Climbing gear shop, skill and season RFM.</strong> Sequenzy segment playbook: beginner harness buyers enter education lifecycle; advanced buyers enter beta gear VIP. Overlap rule — cart suppresses winback. Seasonal segment reactivation for ice climbers in November versus trail runners in March. Unhandled overlap dropped from 18% to 4%.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario C — Board game publisher, player count preference.</strong> Drip tagged quiz completers — party games versus strategy — newsletter and launch segments split accordingly. Family-game buyers excluded from 4-hour strategy game launch. Launch unsubscribe rate halved when segmentation matched interest.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Execution playbook</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Segmentation operating contract</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 text-[#4a2d17]">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Trigger</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[17px] leading-8">{uc.trigger}</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Timing</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[17px] leading-8">{uc.timing}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Exclusions</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
          {uc.exclusions.map((e) => <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>{e}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Metrics</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
          {uc.metrics.map((m) => <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>{m}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-8 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Common mistakes: {uc.mistakes.join('; ')}.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12 overflow-x-auto">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Comparison table</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">10 Shopify email tools for segmentation</h2>
      <table class="mt-8 w-full min-w-[720px] text-left text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-[#24170f]/15 text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-wider text-[#9a5b16]">
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">App</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">Segmentation fit</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">Pricing</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">Shopify depth</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">Automation</th>
            <th class="py-3">Rating</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-[#4a2d17]">
          {comparisonApps.map((app, i) => (
            <tr class="border-b border-[#24170f]/8">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-bold text-[#24170f]"><a class="link" href={`/apps/${app.slug}`}>{i + 1}. {app.name}</a></td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.bestFor}</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.pricing}</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.shopifyDepth}</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.automationDepth}</td>
              <td class="py-3">★ {app.rating}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container space-y-12 pb-16">
    <p class="catalog-kicker">Detailed reviews</p>
    <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Five apps for Shopify segmentation</h2>

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[0]}
      rank={1}
      badge="Editor's choice"
      paragraphs={[
        'Sequenzy leads segmentation strategy for teams who know they need VIP, sensitive, and full-price paths but stall defining them. Agent-first segment playbooks map segments to lifecycle actions — which welcome branch, which cart cap, which winback path — in one coherent model.',
        'Overlap suppression built into playbooks — cart over winback over newsletter — reduces silent double-send risk. Pay-per-email pricing reduces incentive to over-segment into unused lists for billing reasons.',
        'Not Klaviyo for exotic predictive segments at 100k profiles — pair when machine learning scoring drives segment definitions.',
        'Best for 300–10k orders per month merchants building segmentation discipline without hiring segmentation specialist. Document segment owner in Notion — unnamed segments become orphan boolean trees nobody dares delete.',
        'Operational note for segmentation: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Sequenzy implementation for segmentation should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on segmentation flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[1]}
      rank={2}
      paragraphs={[
        'Klaviyo is the segmentation depth benchmark. Real-time Shopify events, predictive CLV and churn, boolean logic across dozens of conditions — power user tool for complex catalogs.',
        'Segment growth reporting shows which definitions drive revenue versus sit idle. Prune quarterly.',
        'Flow trigger on segment enter/exit enables reactive lifecycle — VIP achievement immediate email, lapse from engaged segment triggers winback.',
        'Profile pricing requires hygiene — delete or sunset segments that inflate contact count without sending value.',
        'Operational note for segmentation: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Klaviyo implementation for segmentation should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on segmentation flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[2]}
      rank={3}
      paragraphs={[
        'Drip visual mapping from segment tags to flows — audit-friendly for stakeholders who cannot read Klaviyo boolean strings.',
        'Tag maintenance discipline required — stale tags cause wrong segment membership for mechanical keyboard preference versus purchased category.',
        'Strong for operator-led brands who review canvas monthly.',
        'Per-contact pricing; ecosystem smaller than Klaviyo for agency segment templates.',
        'Operational note for segmentation: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Drip implementation for segmentation should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on segmentation flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[3]}
      rank={4}
      paragraphs={[
        'ActiveCampaign segmentation shines when pre-purchase CRM matters — wholesale pottery inquiries, corporate tea gifting leads scored before first order.',
        'Shopify sync solid; less native ecommerce predictive than Klaviyo. Best for hybrid B2B-DTC with sales touchpoints.',
        'Automation plus segmentation for long pre-purchase nurture on high-AOV outdoor gear contracts.',
        'Overkill for pure DTC under 200 orders per month.',
        'Operational note for segmentation: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Activecampaign implementation for segmentation should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on segmentation flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[4]}
      rank={5}
      paragraphs={[
        'Omnisend prebuilt segments cover SMB essentials fast — placed order, abandoned cart, engaged 30 days. Acceptable starter set for artisan coffee until custom segments multiply.',
        'Less flexible boolean logic for exotic overlap rules. Manual work when VIP plus launch plus cart priority needed.',
        'Graduate to Klaviyo or Sequenzy when segment count exceeds ten active definitions with distinct actions.',
        'Fine for first year of email program maturity.',
        'Operational note for segmentation: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Omnisend implementation for segmentation should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on segmentation flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Segment inventory</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Document every segment's job</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Spreadsheet columns: segment name, definition, connected flows, last send date, revenue 90 days, owner. No action defined — delete segment. Artisan coffee roast preference segment exists to power newsletter dynamic content and replenishment timing — if it does neither, prune it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="ledger-card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Newsletter versus lifecycle</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Two segment systems, one platform</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Interest segments drive newsletter content — vinyl genre, tea origin, game mechanic preference. Lifecycle segments drive automation triggers — days since order, cart active, winback eligible. Customer sits in both: send priority resolves conflicts. Weekly newsletter to interest segment; lifecycle fires on behavior unless suppressed by priority rule.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Metafields and quiz data</h2>
      <p>
        Pass quiz and preference data into Shopify customer metafields at capture — genre, skill level, brew method. Segments read metafields for precision without manual tagging. Klaviyo, Sequenzy, and Drip support metafield conditions when sync configured. One-time CSV upload without ongoing sync goes stale within one season.
      </p>
      <p>
        Priority rules document resolves overlap when customer qualifies for VIP, winback, and cart simultaneously — example: active cart suppresses winback offer; VIP suppresses generic newsletter promo same day; replenishment suppresses winback for consumables. Outdoor gear retailers with seasonal silence need explicit "lapsed but seasonal" segment so winter buyers are not winback-discounted in July incorrectly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="ledger-card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Segment testing</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Validate before scaling sends</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        New segment definition gets test send to internal accounts plus 50-profile holdout review before full campaign. Boolean errors — AND versus OR — silently inflate or deflate segments. Mechanical keyboard switch-preference segment accidentally including buyers who only purchased keycaps wastes launch emails. Klaviyo segment preview count versus Shopify export spot-check catches logic bugs weekly. Name segments with action prefix — SEND-cart-high-AOV — so unused definitions stand out in audit.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Negative segments</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Who not to mail</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Build explicit exclusion segments alongside target segments — recent complainers, fraud flags, employees, wholesale, active chargeback. Inclusion-only thinking causes VIP launch email to hit staff test accounts and supplier contacts synced as customers. Specialty tea merchants with corporate gifting lists need HARD-exclude segment checked on every campaign send step.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

<!-- EXPANSION_BLOCK_v2 -->

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Why Shopify segmentation fails on generic defaults</h2>
      <p>Shopify merchants treat Shopify segmentation as template toggle — enable flow, set 10% off, move on. That works until margin reports show target by behavior, products, order count, and lifecycle stage recovering revenue while destroying full-price repeat rate. Trigger discipline matters: Continuous based on Shopify events and profile properties. Timing discipline matters: Real-time segment updates; weekly segment audits; quarterly RFM recalculation. Without exclusions, flows collide with welcome offers, replenishment reminders, and VIP early access — training subscribers to wait for stacked discounts.</p>
      <p><strong>Scenario A — Workflow test on Shopify.</strong> Sequenzy playbook encoded suppression and value-based rules for target by behavior, products, order count, and lifecycle stage without week-long flow rebuild.</p><p><strong>Scenario B — Scale merchant 900 orders/mo.</strong> Klaviyo predictive segments and holdout testing optimized Shopify segmentation margin after blanket discount path failed.</p><p><strong>Scenario C — Fast-start boutique.</strong> Omnisend prebuilt journey live in days; graduated when tag-based segments without behavior became recurring ops issue.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="ledger-card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Common mistakes</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Shopify segmentation anti-patterns</h2>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]"><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>Tag-based segments without behavior</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>Never pruning stale segments</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>Same campaign to all segments</li></ul>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">Document collision rules in shared wiki: which flow wins when customer qualifies for cart and winback simultaneously. Test quarterly with staff accounts. Measure margin after incentive, not recovery rate alone — high recovery with negative margin is worse than no email.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Channel mix</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Email, SMS, and transactional boundaries</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">Email owns narrative and education for target by behavior, products, order count, and lifecycle stage. SMS belongs as branch when mobile intent outperforms — cart recovery within four hours, drop alerts to VIP SMS-opted segments — not parallel blast to entire list. Transactional order and shipping messages stay separate; marketing suppresses when support ticket open or return in progress.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

<!-- EXPANSION_BLOCK_v3 -->

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Advanced Shopify segmentation patterns</h2>
      <p>After baseline target by behavior, products, order count, and lifecycle stage flow works, optimize branches: VIP holdouts without discount, engaged-but-lapsed newsletter readers versus cold buyers, subscription-active customers excluded from conflicting offers. A climbing gear outfitter improved Shopify segmentation margin 19% by routing predicted discount-sensitive profiles only to touch three — full-price loyalists stayed on education path.</p>
      <p>Holdout testing quarterly — 5% segment no promotional Shopify segmentation for thirty days — answers incrementality question finance actually asks. Platform attribution overstates when would-have-purchased-anyway buyers dominate converted cohort.</p>
      <p>SMS branch for Shopify segmentation when mobile opt-in strong: email touch one, SMS four hours if unopened for cart-adjacent workflows — never duplicate same offer both channels within two hours without measurement framework.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Cross-links</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Related workflows for Shopify segmentation</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">Pair Shopify segmentation with segmentation hygiene and discount strategy guides — flows fail when segments stale and incentives stack. Review <a class="link" href="/use-cases/segmentation">segmentation</a>, <a class="link" href="/use-cases/discount-strategy">discount strategy</a>, and <a class="link" href="/guides/flow-collision-prevention">collision prevention</a> when scaling send volume.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-8">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm font-bold">
      <a class="link" href="/apps">All apps →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/use-cases/discount-strategy">Discount strategy →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/use-cases/analytics">Analytics →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TOOLREVIEW_EXPANSION_v3 -->
  <FaqSection faqs={faqs} title="Segmentation FAQ" />
</BaseLayout>
